Idealised case representative of typical convective conditions in the ocean. Convection is triggered by a surface cooling of Q0=−500 W m−2, corresponding to a surface buoyancy loss of B0=-2.5×10−7 m2 s−3. 

Salinity is kept uniform at S=32.6 psu.
 
The ocean is initially at rest with a constant stratification ΔΘ=1K/1000m, corresponding to 
N2=1.962×10−6 s−2

A uniform wind stress is applied in the meridional direction (u*^2=0.05 m2 s−2)

Each scenario is run for 72 hours, and the final state can be compared with LES data.

For further information, see Perrot and Lemarié (2025).

References:

Perrot, M., Lemarié, F., 2025. Energetically consistent Eddy-Diffusivity Mass-Flux Convective Schemes: 2. Implementation and Evaluation in an oceanic context. J. Adv. Model. Earth Syst. 
doi:https://doi.org/10.1029/2024MS004616.
